            <li>Though I've spoken this language since I was a baby, the nuances and reasoning behind the structure of the english language has eluded me until this class.</li>
            <li>Avoid using "There" and "It" as subjects of a sentence.</li>
            <li>Make sure that the modifier you're implementing is clearly giving information about the correct noun.</li>
            <li>Who is for the subject, whom is for the object. (Usually)</li>
