    <h3>Writing a Message</h3>
    <div class="col-4">
        <h4>PLAN</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><b>P</b>urpose - Decide what you want your audience to know/feel/do after</li>
            <li><b>A</b>udience - Consider cultural, privacy, and security issues of your audience</li>
            <li><b>S</b>trategy - Appeal to the rhetorical strategies of pathos, ethos, and logos</li>
            <li><b>S</b>tructure - Build clear frameworks into your writing</li>



        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4">
        <img src="/img/Plan.jpeg" width="350" style="margin-top:20px;"/>
    </div>
    <div class="col-4">
        <h4>ORGANIZE</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Organize Information - Structure for clarity, and frame the message using outlining</li>
            <li>Outline - <b>Top-Down Approach, Mind Mapping, Bottom-Up Approach</b></li>
            <li>Use the 4A structure - Get <b>A</b>ttention, Give <b>A</b>genda, Present <b>A</b>rgument, Call to <b>A</b>ction </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
